                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 185.1/33</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Tasker H. Bliss</persName> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="27" xml:id="d229fn27">This memorandum bears the notation in Secretary
                        Lansing’s handwriting: “Mr. Grew: I heartily approve this. Ask for reports
                        by Thursday, the 13th RL.”</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-03-11">March 11,
                            1919</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I suggest that the American representative or representatives on each of the
                    Committees appointed by the Peace Conference or by the Council of Ten be
                    instructed to report to the American Delegation, before the arrival of the
                    President, in what respect (if any) the report of his Committee violates (if it
                    does violate) any of the President’s Declarations, and what is the justification
                    for it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tasker H. Bliss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
